(60913, 171014, 5615, 1, 'I Heard You Died', 'I started Writing this song while my uncle Tom was dying, I finished it after he died... \r\nMy uncle had had a death experience many years prior to his passing... He flat lined and was legally dead for a time... saw the white light etc.. but my Aunt Jean wouldn''t let him go and yelled him to come back to life. I found that to be truly fascinating and magical;, Probably why I am still not an atheist.\r\n\r\ncredits\r\nfrom DIY, track released 24 June 2012 \r\n\r\nPat Reid: Electric guitar, vocals, hammond organ, bass \r\nDavid Ramey: Drums \r\nProduced, Engineered by Pat Reid', '2013-08-13 00:00:00', 2012, 1, 0, 7, 'I heard you died\r\nI heard you stepped out of life', '', 155, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 1, 0, '2013-02-11 18:54:06', '2015-03-12 13:59:23', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
